{"ERICA":[{"def":"A genus of shrubby plants, including the heaths, many of them producing beautiful flowers.","pos":""}],"ERICACEOUS":[{"def":"Belonging to the Heath family, or resembling plants of that family; consisting of heats.","pos":""}],"ERICINOL":[{"def":"A colorless oil (quickly becoming brown), with a pleasant odor, obtained by the decomposition of ericolin.","pos":""}],"ERICIUS":[{"def":"The Vulgate rendering of the Hebrew word qipod, which in the \"Authorized Version\" is translated bittern, and in the Revised Version, porcupine.","pos":""}],"ERICOLIN":[{"def":"A glucoside found in the bearberry (and others of the Ericaceæ), and extracted as a bitter, yellow, amorphous mass.","pos":""}],"ERIDANUS":[{"def":"A long, winding constellation extending southward from Taurus and containing the bright star Achernar.","pos":""}],"ERIGIBLE":[{"def":"Capable of being erected.","pos":""}],"ERIN":[{"def":"An early, and now a poetic, name of Ireland.","pos":""}],"ERINACEOUS":[{"def":"Of the Hedgehog family; like, or characteristic of, a hedgehog.","pos":""}],"ERINITE":[{"def":"A hydrous arseniate of copper, of an emerald-green color; -- so called from Erin, or Ireland, where it occurs.","pos":""}],"ERINYS":[{"def":"An avenging deity; one of the Furies; sometimes, conscience personified.","pos":""}],"ERIOMETER":[{"def":"An instrument for measuring the diameters of minute particles or fibers, from the size of the colored rings produced by the diffraction of the light in which the objects are viewed.","pos":""}],"ERISTALIS":[{"def":"A genus of dipterous insects whose young (called rat-tailed larvæ) are remarkable for their long tapering tail, which spiracles at the tip, and for their ability to live in very impure and salt waters; -- also called drone fly.","pos":""}]}